channel.title: Problem(s)
channel.description:
I don't know my router name and pass. I'm working on making a server. I was wondering if I could see my name and pass somewhere in the start menu or control panel or something. Also, if I can even make a server w/o logging into router.
[i]Also...[/i] When I tell my source to compile, it doesn't do it. it says... The system cannot find the path specified. Press any key to continue . . .
I need help please!

item.title: Problem(s)
item.dc:creator: @bib bib
item.description:
@bib wrote:

Step 1: Open up hamachi, if you dont have it download it at hamachi.cc. Open up your client and check on the top of the box for numbers this is your ip for people to go on you
server. it should look like this:

Step 2: Open up your server folder go into runserver open it up it should say starting whatever server on 0:0:0:0:43594 or 0:0:0:0:5555. those numbers at the end are your port and your server ip is the numbers from the top of hamachi.
